   The club practices Gracie Jiu Jitsu and trains primarily in the gi  Gracie Jiu Jitsu is a martial art that has been proven to be an effective method of self defense based on efficiency  patience  and control  The club also affords members the opportunity to compete in gi and no gi tournaments  Participation is restricted to cadets currently on the club roster and any cadets who are enrolled in a PE 315 Combatives course    VMI BRAZILIAN JIU JITSU CLASSIC   Registration Form Keydet Classic Tournament Results VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 